{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c6f4f530-a8a1-43e3-b0b6-100ce0c255b2","content":"\n\nIn .NET 10, `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` still exists but its behavior changed — it now sets padding on the **Page** rather than adjusting the layout bounds, which can conflict if you're also setting `Page.Padding`. The recommended .NET 10 approach is the same property, but be aware of the interaction:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\" ?>\n<ContentPage\n    xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n    xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n    xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n    ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"\n    x:Class=\"MyApp.MainPage\">\n\n    <!-- Do NOT set Padding on the ContentPage — it overrides the safe area insets.\n         If you need extra padding, apply it to your root layout instead. -->\n    <Grid Padding=\"16\">\n        <!-- your content -->\n    </Grid>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**If that still doesn't work** (e.g., you're inside `Shell`), the reliable fallback is to bind padding manually in code-behind:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override void OnAppearing()\n{\n    base.OnAppearing();\n#if IOS\n    var safeInsets = On<Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOS>()\n                        .SafeAreaInsets();\n    Padding = safeInsets;\n#endif\n}\n```\n\n**Key .NET 10 gotchas:**\n- If you set `Padding` on the page in XAML, it **replaces** the safe-area padding instead of merging with it.\n- `Shell` pages may override safe area behavior — use `Shell.NavBarIsVisible=\"True\"` or the code-behind approach above.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"146f8b13-9b4d-4c7b-bd54-7c347de70b22","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET MAUI migration issue from .NET 9 to .NET 10 regarding safe area handling on iOS. This is a knowledge question about a framework change.\n\nIn .NET 10 (which would be a